      "content": "It's completely normal to feel what you're feeling, and it's okay to take breaks and not want to keep pretending everything's alright. Grief can be an incredibly lonely and exhausting experience. I’m here for you whenever you need to talk. Hold on to the things that can bring you a bit of comfort and mirror of his presence — like memories, photos, or the routine of your daily life — at your own pace. You've experienced unimaginable loss, and it's okay not to be okay. You're not alone in this.",
      "source": "target",
